{
  "genre": "reggae",
  "mode": "focus",
  "mixStrategy": "FREQUENCY SEPARATION: Bass (Electric Bass, GM 33) owns 20-300Hz with MIDI 31-43 (G1-G2), providing the heavy foundation with dotted quarter-note reggae feel on root-5th patterns. Chords (Organ, GM 16) fill 300Hz-2kHz with MIDI 60-72 offbeat skank voicings \u2014 completely silent on downbeats, hitting every upbeat 'and' to create the signature reggae pulse. Melody (Nylon Guitar, GM 24) sits in 1-5kHz with MIDI 60-76, playing simple repetitive vocal-style hooks that breathe between the skank hits. Drums (GM 0 ch10) provide the one-drop foundation: kick ONLY on beat 3, rim click on beats 2 and 4, hi-hat on 8th notes throughout.\n\nRHYTHMIC INTERLOCK: The bass locks tightly with the kick on beat 3 and provides weight on beat 1. The organ skank fills every upbeat ('and'), creating the classic reggae chop. The melody floats above, playing longer sustained phrases that move between chord tones on strong beats and scale tones on weak beats. The hi-hat provides the steady 8th-note pulse that glues everything together.\n\nHARMONIC UNITY: All tracks follow the same I-IV progression (G-C) in G Mixolydian, changing together every 2 bars (6.4 seconds). The 6-segment energy arc (0.4\u21920.6\u21920.7\u21920.7\u21920.7\u21920.5) is achieved by: Segment 1 (0-7.5s) \u2014 sparse intro, bass+hats only entering; Segment 2 (7.5-15s) \u2014 full band enters with moderate velocity; Segments 3-5 (15-37.5s) \u2014 full energy plateau with consistent density for focus habituation; Segment 6 (37.5-45s) \u2014 gentle pullback, fewer melody notes, softer velocities.\n\nFOCUS MODE DESIGN: Velocities stay in 45-75 range (except bass at 80-90 for weight and kick at 85). Note durations are 1-4 seconds for melody and bass. The repetitive I-IV progression and consistent rhythmic pattern create a steady, predictable texture that habituates quickly, perfect for focus.",
